        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 23 at 3:15PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 315 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Saguache, or 42 miles north of Alamosa, moving southeast at 55 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Saguache.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
